64static const ENUMERATED_NAMES crl_reasons[] = {
65{CRL_REASON_UNSPECIFIED, "Unspecified", "unspecified"},
66{CRL_REASON_KEY_COMPROMISE, "Key Compromise", "keyCompromise"},
67{CRL_REASON_CA_COMPROMISE, "CA Compromise", "CACompromise"},
68{CRL_REASON_AFFILIATION_CHANGED, "Affiliation Changed", "affiliationChanged"},
69{CRL_REASON_SUPERSEDED, "Superseded", "superseded"},
70{CRL_REASON_CESSATION_OF_OPERATION,
71 "Cessation Of Operation", "cessationOfOperation"},
72{CRL_REASON_CERTIFICATE_HOLD, "Certificate Hold", "certificateHold"},
73{CRL_REASON_REMOVE_FROM_CRL, "Remove From CRL", "removeFromCRL"},
74{CRL_REASON_PRIVILEGE_WITHDRAWN, "Privilege Withdrawn", "privilegeWithdrawn"},
75{CRL_REASON_AA_COMPROMISE, "AA Compromise", "AACompromise"},
76{-1, NULL, NULL}
77};
78
79const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_crl_reason = {
80NID_crl_reason, 0, ASN1_ITEM_ref(ASN1_ENUMERATED),
810,0,0,0,
82(X509V3_EXT_I2S)i2s_ASN1_ENUMERATED_TABLE,
830,
840,0,0,0,
85(void *)crl_reasons};
86
87
88char *i2s_ASN1_ENUMERATED_TABLE(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method,
89 ASN1_ENUMERATED *e)
90{
91 const ENUMERATED_NAMES *enam;
92 long strval;
93 strval = ASN1_ENUMERATED_get(e);
94 for(enam = method->usr_data; enam->lname; enam++) {
95 if(strval == enam->bitnum) return BUF_strdup(enam->lname);
96 }
97 return i2s_ASN1_ENUMERATED(method, e);
98}
